<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-653-840  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 653 840.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>LAN Times  July 1990 v7 n8 p145(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Views 2.0: infobase manager. (from Folio Corp.) (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Germann, Christopher.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Folio Corp will introduce version 2.0 of its Views and PreViewsinformation retrieval packages in late summer 1990.andP;  Both packageswill offer greatly increased speed and new features including apull-down menu, hypertext linking of indexed files, and theability to open and search multiple infobases, proprietary fileformats that integrate text with an index to the text.andP;  Indexingcompression means that an infobase is often 50 percent the size ofthe original text file.andP;  Both Views and PreViews can stay residentin a 10Kbyte segment of memory while another application isaccessed.andP;  On a local area network, an infobase's creator can makeon-line changes to the infobase that will be immediatelyaccessible to all users.andP;  A true multiuser version of the softwareis in the planning stages.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Folio Corp. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Views 2.0 (Computer program) (product introduction)PreVIEWS 2.0 (Search software) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Software PackagesInformation Storage and RetrievalInformation Resources ManagementProduct Introduction.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>